21
00:02:20,106 --> 00:02:20,828
For what reason?

22
00:02:21,468 --> 00:02:26,414
Because, listeners, this samsara is without discoverable beginning.

23
00:02:27,036 --> 00:02:35,266
A first point is not discerned of beings wandering and roaming on, hindered by ignorance and fettered by cravings.

24
00:02:36,141 --> 00:02:43,012
For such a long time you have experienced suffering, anguish and disaster and swell the cemeteries.

25
00:02:43,894 --> 00:02:55,711
It is enough to become disenchanted with formations, enough to become dispassionate towards them, enough to become liberated for them.

26
00:02:55,731 --> 00:02:58,816
So samsara is just the world of onward going.

27
00:02:58,895 --> 00:03:00,078
It's just a way of saying that.

28
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:03,263
You know, the world just keeps turning and turning.

29
