I mean, there's not much difference between what happened at the beginning of the dawn of human consciousness and what's happening now.

50
00:05:50,973 --> 00:05:54,459
And this is because of greed, hatred and delusion.

51
00:05:54,980 --> 00:06:24,901
now in the east and in fact before Christianity Judeo-Christian civilization it would have been the same for the Greeks and the Romans the idea was much more cyclical so time revolves and of course you can see that in a sense that every day the sun rises and the sun sets and you know there's this cyclic and when you get the idea of a cycle there's no beginning there's no end it just keeps going on and on and on so it's a very different idea about what time is you see

52
00:06:25,016 --> 00:06:31,307
Now, what was horrific to the people in the Buddha's time was that there didn't seem to be an end to it.

53
00:06:32,007 --> 00:06:34,432
That this was what was in store.

54
00:06:35,293 --> 00:06:46,350
Every life, every time you ended a lifetime, depending on your beliefs, some people believed your next life would be determined by your good actions.

55
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:48,442
by what you did or what you didn't do.

56
00:06:48,822 --> 00:06:51,425
Some people believed it was just fate.

57
00:06:51,946 --> 00:06:54,850
So next lifetime, you ended up as a pig.

58
00:06:55,711 --> 00:06:56,211
And that was it.

59
00:06:56,752 --> 00:06:58,793
And then the next lifetime, I'd be human again.

60
00:06:59,535 --> 00:07:01,877
And for some people, it made no sense at all.

61
00:07:01,898 --> 00:07:05,521
For others, there was some idea of progression.

62
00:07:06,923 --> 00:07:10,668
That one went on and then went into higher realms.

63
00:07:10,869 --> 00:07:13,771
There was, of course, people who were annihilationists.

64
00:07:14,139 --> 00:07:42,476
you know this is the Buddha's time where when your life was finished that was it it was complete others thought you went up to this very high realm and then that was it cut off so there's masses of ideas but the general thing was that was there a way out of this see so that's that's the Buddha's that's what he means by at its basic thing about dukkha about suffering was there a way out of this onward going and that's what the word samsara means okay

65
00:07:42,759 --> 00:07:46,884
So, he says, there's no discoverable beginning, you see.

66
00:07:47,944 --> 00:07:50,646
But then he points, of course, to an end, you see.

67
00:07:51,548 --> 00:08:00,677
I mean, the reason is, of course, because of this hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving.

68
00:08:01,197 --> 00:08:05,141
So, the ignorance, remember, is not knowing who or what we really are.

69
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:09,644
In so doing, we make the mistake, we think we are what we appear to be.

70
00:08:10,064 --> 00:08:13,713
