75
00:08:26,406 --> 00:08:27,648
When you're disenchanted.

76
00:08:28,288 --> 00:08:34,235
So when you fall in love with somebody, you know, there is that complete enchantment with the other.

77
00:08:34,255 --> 00:08:38,562
Their voice, the way they walk, the way their hair is.

78
00:08:39,182 --> 00:08:40,703
That's why nobody fell in love with me, you see.

79
00:08:43,847 --> 00:08:51,057
So, where they see that, and then suddenly, of course, about three months on, or six months on, something goes off.

80
00:08:51,965 --> 00:09:11,965
and there's a disenchantment and suddenly they just yes to be enchanted is actually a word coming from witchcraft you're drawn into you're enchanted you're drawn into you're being mesmerized enchanted you see

81
00:09:13,327 --> 00:09:23,962
So to become disenchanted with something, to become dispassionate, in other words, not to have these feelings about craving and all that sort of stuff around things.

82
00:09:24,884 --> 00:09:28,909
And then finally, it's enough to be liberated from them.

83
00:09:28,929 --> 00:09:42,610
And of course, that liberation really means this complete disidentification and dispossession, mental dispossession of everything that's in this world.

84
00:09:43,028 --> 00:10:11,279
and that's what we mean by renunciation now remember we're talking about a relationship we're not talking about the actual things we're not talking about not eating pleasant food anymore we're talking about not having this wrong relationship with pleasant food you've got to be careful easy and else you end up you know just dying of starvation because you think you've got to give up food no you don't have to give up any food

85
00:10:12,442 --> 00:10:16,666
And then, of course, he says the same thing for fathers, so both mothers and fathers.

86
00:10:21,451 --> 00:10:23,854
But that's an interesting thing for us, isn't it?

87
00:10:23,874 --> 00:10:27,456
The idea of time, how we perceive time.

88
